<paragraph id="A23B8905FF94FFB30CEAFD35FDE1FC95" blockId="4.[151,1436,721,820]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
This is the single fossil species described for the genus 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF94FFB30F5CFD35FC71FD4D" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[801,966,721,747]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF94FFB30F5CFD35FC71FD4D" box="[801,966,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Clystopsenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Together with † 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF94FFB308F0FD36FA2BFD4D" baseAuthorityName="Prentice &amp; Poinar" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[1165,1436,722,747]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Pristapenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inopinata">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF94FFB308F0FD36FA2BFD4D" box="[1165,1436,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Pristapenesia inopinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Prentice &amp; Poinar in 
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF94FFB30DF2FD11FDC1FCB6" author="Prentice, M. A. &amp; Poinar Jr., G. O. &amp; Milki, R." box="[399,630,757,784]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" pagination="802 - 811" refId="ref7294" refString="Prentice, M. A., Poinar Jr., G. O. &amp; Milki, R. (1996) Fossil scolebythids (Hymenoptera, Scolebythidae) from Lebanese and Dominican amber. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 98, 802 - 811." type="journal article" year="1996">
Prentice 
<emphasis id="90F05517FF94FFB30D8EFD12FD9CFCA9" box="[499,555,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">et al.</emphasis>
, 1996
</bibRefCitation>
), they represent the two species of 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF94FFB3087FFD11FB16FCA9" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1963" box="[1026,1185,757,783]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scolebythidae</taxonomicName>
known from the Miocene amber of 
<collectingCountry id="DA93C995FF94FFB30D40FCFDFE55FC95" box="[317,482,793,819]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic.
</paragraph>
